headline.main: DOCTORING' OF FILMS FOR NAZIS RELATED; Spy Trial Witness Says the FBI Made Ship Data Valueless

lead_paragraph: The Brooklyn espionage trial entered its fifth week yesterday, with William G. Sebold, counter-espionage agent for the Federal Bureau of Investigation, still on the witness stand giving evidence against the sixteen persons accused of espionage and failure to register as agents of a foreign government.
abstract: Sebold identifies films of naval and commercial ships furnished by Waalen, doctored by FBI agents and sent by E Strunck to German agent in Lisbon
